law.text:
It shall be unlawful for a handler of milk in this state to:
Receive or buy milk from permitted producers or their agents without obtaining a license for each location where milk is received or handled;
Receive milk that is paid for on the basis of weight or volume without having it sampled and weighed or measured by a licensed sampler-weigher;
Manipulate weights, measurements, or tests that are to be used as a basis to purchase milk;
Use false or incorrect records of weights or tests as a basis for payment;
Receive milk purchased from permitted producers by a milk handler that does not have a license to handle;
Use weighing, mixing, sampling, or testing equipment which is inaccurate or nonstandard;
Fail to comply with administrative regulations for weighing, measuring, sampling, and testing milk issued by the director;
Fail to keep records of weights and tests as required by administrative regulation or fail to make such records available for inspection by the director;
Receive milk which is paid for on the basis of tests without having it tested by a licensed tester;
Fail to notify the director in writing of any knowledge of an inaccurately calibrated bulk milk tank; or
Hinder or obstruct any authorized person in the performance of his or her duties under KRS 260.775 to 260.845.
